emphasize /ˈɛmfəˌsaɪz/

(emphasizing,emphasized,emphasizes) BRIT also  emphasise 

1. V-T To emphasize something means to indicate that it is particularly important or true, or to draw special attention to it. 强调 

例： But it's also been emphasized that no major policy changes can be expected to come out of the meeting. 但是也强调，这次会议预期不会做出重大政策改变。

